### 2 assessments (also useful for developing as PM)

There are 2 assessments I think are great for product managers and aspiring product managers.

The first one is PMwheel by [Petra Wille](https://www.petra-wille.com/ "https://www.petra-wille.com/"), author of the book [Strong Product People](https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/56866234-strong-product-people "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/56866234-strong-product-people").

Here is 2 resources on PMwheel:

-   [The PMwheel ‚Äì a Compass for the Product Manager Development Journey](https://www.petra-wille.com/blog/the-pmwheel-a-compass-for-the-product-manager-development-journey "https://www.petra-wille.com/blog/the-pmwheel-a-compass-for-the-product-manager-development-journey")
-   [How to use the PMwheel as a Self-Assessment Tool for Product Managers](https://www.petra-wille.com/blog/how-to-use-the-pmwheel-as-a-self-assessment-tool-for-product-managers "https://www.petra-wille.com/blog/how-to-use-the-pmwheel-as-a-self-assessment-tool-for-product-managers")

The second one is by [Sillicon Valley Product Group](https://www.svpg.com/ "https://www.svpg.com/") and Marty Cagan, author of Inspired.

More information is available here: [Coaching Tools ‚Äì The Assessment](https://www.svpg.com/coaching-tools-the-assessment/ "https://www.svpg.com/coaching-tools-the-assessment/")
